				\begin{document}$${\text{NADH}} \to {\text{NAD}}^{ + } + {\text{H}}^{ + } + 2{\text{e}}^{ - }$$\end{document}). Then, for each mentioned condition, the flux variability for each reaction was determined (Fig. 1), and two criteria were applied to identify the candidate reactions for up or down regulations.Figure 1
Comparison of flux variability for each reaction at the minimum and maximum rates of NADH production reaction to finding appropriate reactions for (A) up-regulation, and (B) down-regulation. Compared rates were highlighted in red.

In all experiments, after five days of cultivation, cyanobacterial cells were harvested during exponential growth (OD750=3.5±0.1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
