				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$OD_{750 } = 3.5 \pm 0.1$$\end{document}), the potential reduction can be attributed to the depletion of nutrients; thus, fresh medium injection compensates for the potential drop. This phenomenon was also shown previously in the work of Madiraju et al.19, in which replenishing minerals led to an increase in power density. Moreover, for the culture media with activator, this abrupt growth in the OCP was higher than the sole culture medium of BG-11. A comparison between Fig. 4A, B reveal that the culture medium of Synechocystis + BG-11 + 40 mM NH4Cl obtained the higher OCP and more prolonged stationary phase. This issue puts the emphasis on the more impact of this culture medium on the cell potential compared to the BG-11 + 50 mM KCl.
